# Tailwind CSS v4 Style & Architecture Discipline

## Critical Rule: Config File Invalidation
- NEVER create or suggest a tailwind.config.js or tailwind.config.ts file. Tailwind v4 has completely deprecated javascript-based configurations.
- All theme customizations, custom colors, and plugins MUST be declared inside the main CSS file using the new @theme directive.

## Implementation Standard

### 1. Theme Customization (The 2026 CSS-First Way)
When the user asks to add custom colors or breakpoints, inject them exactly like this inside the CSS entry point:

'''css
@import "tailwindcss";

@theme {
  --color-brand-primary: #ff5a5f;
  --color-brand-dark: #111111;
  --breakpoint-xs: 30rem;
}
'''

### 2. Forbidden Classes (v3 vs v4 Delta)
- DO NOT use @apply for complex utilities unless explicitly requested. v4's compiler optimized inline utility execution speed by 5x.
- DO NOT use bg-opacity-* or text-opacity-*. In v4, use the modern slash alpha syntax directly: bg-black/50 or text-brand-primary/80.
